<subSubSection id="B2D6B2DC4117E9136B9DD3A4FD5A244A" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FA73E1574117E9136B9DD3A4FD5A244A" blockId="63.[151,1437,151,1943]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454117E9136B9DD3A4FE912782" bold="true" box="[199,326,1484,1508]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Etymology</emphasis>
. This conspicuous species is dedicated to Alexandr P. Rasnitsyn (
<collectingRegion id="38082FB54117E9136F78D3A4FB5F2782" box="[1058,1160,1484,1508]" country="Russia" name="Moscow" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Moscow</collectingRegion>
), who contributed and at an age of 80 years still contributes fundamentally to the knowledge in diversity and phylogeny of extant and fossil insects, among them the basal 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44117E9136AB7D07CFD5E244A" box="[493,649,1556,1580]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Hymenoptera</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
