<subSubSection id="B2D6B2DC4117E9136B9DD0EBFAF625F1" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FA73E1574117E9136B9DD0EBFF092529" blockId="63.[151,1437,151,1943]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454117E9136B9DD0EBFEE324FD" bold="true" box="[199,308,1667,1691]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Remarks</emphasis>
. The female of 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44117E9136ABFD0EBFD4D24FC" authorityName="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer" authorityYear="2013" box="[485,666,1667,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rasnitsyni">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454117E9136ABFD0EBFD4D24FC" box="[485,666,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Xyela rasnitsyni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares its sharply pointed tip of valvula 3 with 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44117E9136FF6D0EBFF0F24D9" authority="(Benson, 1961)" baseAuthorityName="Benson" baseAuthorityYear="1961" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvetica">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454117E9136FF6D0EBFAE724FD" box="[1196,1328,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">X. helvetica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64117E9136E1AD0EAFF0724D9" author="Benson, R. B." pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="161 - 195" refId="ref66513" refString="Benson, R. B. (1961) The sawflies (Hymenoptera Symphyta) of the Swiss National Park and surrounding area. Ergebnisse der wissenschaftlichen Untersuchungen im Schweizerischen Nationalpark, 7, 161 - 195." type="journal article" year="1961">Benson, 1961</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44117E9136A43D0C0FD9224D9" authority="Dalman, 1819" authorityName=", Dalman" authorityYear="1819" box="[281,581,1703,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longula">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454117E9136A43D0C0FE4424D9" box="[281,403,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">X. longula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64117E9136AC4D0CFFD9224D9" author="Dalman, J. W." box="[414,581,1703,1727]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="117 - 127" refId="ref67724" refString="Dalman, J. W. (1819) Nagra nya Insect-Genera. Svenska Vetenskaps Akademiens Handlingar, pp. 117 - 127." type="book chapter" year="1819">Dalman, 1819</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which are Western Palearctic. However, the latter have article 3 of the maxillary palp shorter than the scape (in 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44117E9136907D0A3FD3E2484" authorityName="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer" authorityYear="2013" box="[605,745,1739,1762]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rasnitsyni">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454117E9136907D0A3FD3E2484" box="[605,745,1739,1762]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">X. rasnitsyni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
1.45–1.60 times longer than scape), and the valvula 3 straight (slightly bent downwards) and diamond-shaped in cross section (compressed). The male is easily distinguished from other forms occurring in this region by the harpes, which are longer than wide (in other species as long as wide).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA73E1574117E9136B9DD133FAF625F1" blockId="63.[151,1437,151,1943]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
In 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C74117E9136BBFD132FEE52514" box="[229,306,1882,1906]" name="Russia" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Russia</collectingCountry>
, A.P. Rasnitsyn collected 
<specimenCount id="ECCA2ADE4117E913690CD132FD342514" box="[598,739,1882,1906]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" type="female">four females</specimenCount>
from 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44117E9136872D133FC352515" authorityName="Sieb. &amp; Zucc. (Rasnitsyn" authorityYear="1965" box="[808,994,1883,1907]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="koraiensis">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454117E9136872D133FC352515" box="[808,994,1883,1907]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Pinus koraiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and at least the specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C74117E9136E03D132FA4B2514" box="[1369,1436,1882,1906]" name="China" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">China</collectingCountry>
were collected close to this pine species (E.-J. Fittkau, personal communication, see also 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44117E9136F24D1E8FAC725F1" authorityName="Sieb. &amp; Zucc. (Rasnitsyn" authorityYear="1965" box="[1150,1296,1919,1943]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="koraiensis">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454117E9136F24D1E8FAC725F1" box="[1150,1296,1919,1943]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">X. koraiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
